  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf first UserA sets `Show your profile picture to: Contacts` and UserB is a contact of UserA, but after that UserA changes this setting to `Show your profile picture to: None`, then UserB will still see the profile picture of UserB.\r\nBut if UserA first changes the settings to `Show your profile picture to: None`, and then started a chat with UserB, then UserB will not see UserA's profile photo.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n- UserB can't see UserA's profile picture after changing the setting or deleting UserB from contacts\r\n- **As a temporary solution, there may be a warning to users that they will not be able to hide their profile picture for users who have already seen their profile picture (add some explanation to the `Show my picture to` screen** (suggested [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/11768#issuecomment-931240752)))\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nOnce seen by another user, the profile picture cannot be hidden\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Add profile photo\r\n2. Add UserB to contacts and start 1-1 chat\r\n3. UserB adds UserA to contacts\r\n4. UserA: Settings > Privacy and security > `Show your PP to: None` (or delete UserB from contacts)\r\n5. UserB: check profile photo of UserA\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 4/10\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
